\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... The reason I've gathered you all here is none
other than to have a very important discussion with you.

\N<Zuuteruka>But first, we must acknowledge the hardships you've all
endured. You've all done very well.

\N<Zuuteruka>Parents, siblings, sons and daughters, and even lovers who
care for each other. Many of you have been torn apart from
various people, or have even lost them to death.

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, you all are admirable; I couldn't have endured it
myself.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>However... the grueling training sessions that have
tormented you are finally coming to an end. As everyone
knows, it concluded with Rozaro's victory here.

\N<Zuuteruka>The long and painful battle has finally come to a joyous
end.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>Now... that being said, it's not like we're just going to
say 'goodbye' and go our separate ways. This city is moving
on to the next phase.
\N<Segi>The next... phase?

\N<Zuuteruka>As you know, the purpose of the training sessions was to
select and recruit the strong. And now, the strong have been
decided.

\N<Zuuteruka>In other words, it means that most of the men here are
losers who don't have the strength to protect their families
or lovers—pathetic weaklings.
\N<Segi>...

\N<Zuuteruka>The strong will follow a path befitting the strong. The weak
will receive measures appropriate for the weak. That's how
Luda does things.

\N<Zuuteruka>In other words... all men other than the strong are
essentially useless.

\N<Zuuteruka>The losers and useless weaklings will be forced into labor
in Luda-controlled areas. The women will be transferred to
the main force, where they'll bear children for us, the
strong of Luda.
\N<Segi>Wha...!!??
\N<Resident>Th-that's absurd...!?

\N<Zuuteruka>Absurd? I just explained the reason. The strong and the
losers... each has their own role to play.
\N<Resident>Don't joke with me! How can we accept such a thing!?
\N<Resident>Gah...!!??
\N<Segi>Eh...!?

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe, you should have shown that spirit in the battles of
the training sessions. But then again, if you could have
done that, you wouldn't be losers, would you?
\N<Resident>Such a thing... just when I thought it was all over...
\N<Resident>No... I can't take any more of this...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Some women managed to escape, huh? Well, that's to
be expected, isn't it?

\N<Zuuteruka>Just when they thought peace had finally arrived, they're
announced to yet another hellish ordeal.
\N<Zuuteruka>But, well... this was all anticipated.

\N<Zuuteruka>To the weakling men standing here with dumbstruck faces,
wallowing in despair, I have some good news for you.

\N<Zuuteruka>The women who fled from here just now... go capture them and
bring them back.

\N<Zuuteruka>If you do that, I won't hold you accountable for your
crimes. I'll even overlook the forced labor. Depending on
your results, I might even consider recruiting you into
Luda.
\N<Resident>What...!?
\N<Zuuteruka>Don't stand there dumbfounded. Get moving already.

\N<Zuuteruka>Forced labor with an uncertain future can be avoided just by
capturing the women who escaped. It's because you can't act
quickly in times like these that you're weaklings.
\N<Resident>Damn it...!?

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... Weaklings should at least try to show some dignity
as men, shouldn't they?
A
\N<Segi><Segi>Stop it! Stop such reckless behavior right now!

\N<Zuuteruka><Zuuteruka>Well, wait a minute. There's more to the story.

\N<Segi><Segi>What did you say...!?

\N<Irime><Irime>Hurry up and spit it out, it's not going to be

\N<Zuuteruka><Zuuteruka>Don't rush me, I'm about to explain.

\N<Woman><Woman>Please wait... that's impossible...! There's no way

\N<Zuuteruka><Zuuteruka>Right, Segi? And you too, Irime. You must have

\N<Segi><Segi>Mind. Luda...!

\N<Woman><Woman>What do you mean...? Don't tell me the two of

\N<Segi><Segi>...
\N<Irime><Irime>...
\N<Rame><Rame>Mama...

\N<Zuuteruka><Zuuteruka>Hehehe, I'll give as much as the hopefuls want.
If it becomes your strength, then so be it.

\N<Zuuteruka><Zuuteruka>We're not demons or devils; we don't intend to

\N<Zuuteruka><Zuuteruka>The training exercises and our stationing in this

\N<Zuuteruka><Zuuteruka>You either die now... or spend your life as our

\N<Segi><Segi>...

\N<Irime><Irime>Wait a minute! That thing has terrible side

\N<Woman><Woman>I'll take it! I don't care what you say! Even if

\N<Zuuteruka><Zuuteruka>Hehehe, that's right. Believe it or not, it's

\N<Segi><Segi>Please wait! What Irime-san is saying is true! That

\N<Woman><Woman>Shut up! You drank it, didn't you?! Are you

\N<Segi><Segi>No! That's not what I mean at all...!

\N<Woman>Otherwise, I'll eventually die! Become their plaything,

\N<Woman>So what's wrong with betting on the slightest chance of

\N<Segi>That's...!

\N<Irime>Segi, it's useless. In a way, what they're saying makes
sense. We can't interfere now that things have come to this.
\N<Segi>But that's... because of that, we...

\N<Irime>Just as he said. Die now or later, or bet on the chance of

\N<Segi>Irime-san...
That's right. I don't have the right to stop anyone.

In fact, my body was enhanced by the power of that spirit

I can't deny the choices of others when I myself have

I can't save those who are trying to escape one hell only to

Even if they go through horrific experiences, I can't convey

I can't do anything... I'm powerless...

\N<Zuuteruka>Hehehe... looks like we've come to an agreement. Well,
